text: NGC 446 is a lenticular galaxy of type (R)SAB0^0 located in the constellation Pisces. It was first discovered on October 23, 1864 by Albert Marth (and later listed as NGC 446); it was also seen on August 20, 1892 by Stéphane Javelle (and later listed as IC 89). It was described by Dreyer as "faint, very small, stellar." ==References== ==External links== * 0446 18641023 Category:Pisces (constellation) Category:Lenticular galaxies
